Durban - Two Tongaat youngsters were killed after the vehicle they were travelling in collided head-on with a sugar cane truck on Watson Highway in Tongaat on Saturday evening. The funeral service of Thiren Naidoo, 19,of Fairbreeze is expected to take place on Monday. The second victim Shailin Bheem, 19, from Plein Street, will take place on Tuesday. According to Paul Herbst from IPSS Medical Rescue the victims were travelling in the direction of the Tongaat CBD. "On arrival both occupants were severely entrapped in the wreckage. All emergency services worked to extricate both victims." Herbst said one victim died on scene and the other victim was placed on a manual ventilator and died on arrival at the Victoria Hospital. He said the driver of the sugar cane truck sustained no injuries and the road had been closed to traffic. Shailin is the son of Shane and Anitha Bheem who own Bheems Hiring. KZN police spokesperson Captain Nqobile Gwala said a case of culpable homicide was opened. "The circumstances surrounding the incident are being investigated," said Gwala. POST